Lesotho is a patriarchal society. Women are expected to be submissive to their husbands. They are also expected to be obedient and respectful to their in-laws. Women are not allowed to inherit property. They are also not allowed to own land. Women are not allowed to make decisions on their own. They are expected to consult their husbands before making any decisions.
